MultiChoice has launched a DStv self-service app for Android and iOS. The app lets South African DStv subscribers manage their accounts from their smartphone. While DStv had an app in the App Store for iOS devices, it had last been updated in August 2015. MultiChoice reused its existing app listing on the App Store for the new self-service app, while the Android app was published using a fresh listing. The company said that the app offers the following features: Images of the appâ€™s interface are shown below. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-299562" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/DStv-self-service-app-screenshots.jpg" alt="DStv self-service app screenshots" width="640" height="533" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/DStv-self-service-app-screenshots.jpg 720w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/DStv-self-service-app-screenshots-480x400.jpg 480w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/DStv-self-service-app-screenshots-516x430.jpg 516w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" />